<subSubSection id="C33C09E7FFE2FFBB6488689CFD7DBA56" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B995A6CFFE2FFBB6488689CFD7DBA56" blockId="9.[151,756,416,823]" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB6488689CFEBBB8D6" bold="true" box="[151,265,416,439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Remarks:</emphasis>
This is the second Moluccan species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB648868FCFF4CB8B6" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1845" box="[151,254,448,471]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB648868FCFF4CB8B6" box="[151,254,448,471]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Baeocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remaining unnamed, in absence of at least 
<specimenCount id="9D2091E5FFE2FFBB648868DCFEB2B896" box="[151,256,480,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
specimen (see “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB65D668DCFDCDB896" box="[457,639,480,503]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB65D668DCFD82B896" box="[457,560,480,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Baeocera</emphasis>
sp. A
</taxonomicName>
” in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7279DFFE2FFBB66A568DCFF6FBB76" author="Lobl I." pageId="9" pageNumber="112" pagination="165 - 187" refId="ref11281" refString="Lobl I. 2015 a. Contribution to the knowledge of the Scaphidiinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) of the Moluccas. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 8: 165 - 187." type="journal article" year="2015">Löbl, 2015a</bibRefCitation>
). It is similar to the Papuan 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB660A6B3CFD42BB76" authority="Lobl, 2002" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2002" box="[533,752,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB660A6B3CFDDFBB76" box="[533,621,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">B. curta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7279DFFE2FFBB66696B3CFD42BB76" author="Lobl I." box="[630,752,512,535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref11223" refString="Lobl I. 2002. On Baeocera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Scaphidiinae) of New Guinea. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen entomologischen Gesellschaft 75: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2002">Löbl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differs by the less arcuate suture of the metanepisterna and the ventrite I lacking basal striae. Thus, it may be an undescribed species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB65BC6B5CFDF9BB16" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2002" box="[419,587,608,631]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB65BC6B5CFDF9BB16" box="[419,587,608,631]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Baeocera curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a complex aedeagus providing reliable specific characters which are quite unlike those of members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB66926B9CFF7EBBB6" baseAuthorityName="Lobl" baseAuthorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenta">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB66926B9CFF7EBBB6" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Baeocera lenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB65796BFCFE7CBBB6" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2014" box="[358,462,704,727]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agostii">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB65796BFCFE7CBBB6" box="[358,462,704,727]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">B. agostii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen has slightly prominent apical inner apical angles of the elytra, a character noted for the first time in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB66076A3CFDCCBA76" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1845" box="[536,638,768,791]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB66076A3CFDCCBA76" box="[536,638,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Baeocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It may be sexual, as it is in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE2FFBB65E16A23FD7DBA56" authority="Leach." authorityName="Leach." box="[510,719,799,823]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE2FFBB65E16A23FDCDBA56" box="[510,639,799,823]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Scaphisoma</emphasis>
Leach.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
